-- Sidi Kerir Unit Gets 5 Offers for Ethylene Project, Al Mal Says
-- B y   D a h l i a   K h o l a i f
-- 2012-05-22T08:06:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/sidi-kerir-unit-gets-5-offers-for-ethylene-project-al-mal-says.html
Egyptian Co. for Ethylene Production,
a unit of  Sidi Kerir Petrochemicals Co. (SKPC) , received five offers
for construction of a polyethylene plant,  Al-Mal  reported,
citing Ahmed Helmi, the unitâ€™s chairman.  The company has government approval to obtain a bridge loan
of $240 million, part of total loan finance of $1.25 billion
sought for the project, the newspaper said. The plant, which
will have a capacity of 400,000 tons a year, will be built in
the coastal city of Alexandria, Al Mal said.  Egyptian Co. will sign in a few days an agreement with five
local banks for the $1.25 billion, including National Bank of
Egypt, Commercial International Bank of Egypt, Arab African
International Bank, Banque du Caire and  Banque Misr , the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
